                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-09T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 9, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—4:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>317. Following from Reuter, Changchun, March 8th: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The ex-Emperor <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Hsuan Tung</persName> arrived
                            here by special train at 3 p.m. today and was greeted at the station by
                            the Japanese Consul General, General <persName corresp="#p_MC1">Ma
                                Chan-shan</persName> and others, who bowed three times as the
                            ex-Emperor alighted followed by his consort and two other ladies. The
                            ‘Regent Designated’ immediately proceeded to the municipal headquarters,
                            which he is occupying as his residence.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
